        Official Singles Chart on 21/10/2016

        21 October 2016 - 27 October 2016

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        the beatles have 20 hot 100 #1's, the all time record in the u.s. and their 1st year chart run on the hot 100 chart in 1964 is still legendary...here's a look @ all their u.s. #1's and various 1964 hits that had them flooding the top 10 all thruout the year.

        1. 'i want to hold your hand' *enters on 1/18/1964* @ #45-3-1!! spends 7 wks @ #1 and becomes the hot 100 #1 song of the year for 1964.

        2. 'she loves you' *enters on 1/25/1964* @ #69-21-7-3-2-2-2-2-1. spends 2 wks @ #1

        3. 'please please me' *enters on 2/1/1964* @ #68-57-45-29-6-4-3 *final peak*

        4. 'twist and shout' *enters on 3/14/1964 @ #55-7-3-2!! *final peak* on 4/4/1964 the beatles occupy entire top 5, still an unmatched feat.

        5. 'can't buy me love' *enters on 3/28/1964* @ #27-1!! spends 5 wks @ #1.

        6. 'love me do' *enters on 4/11/1964* @ #81-73-67-32-12-3-2-1. spends 1 wk @ #1.

        Sunshine Gal

        24th October 2016
